cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language processing and parsing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep contextualized word embeddings and ensembling parsers.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of a natural language processing system.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural network-based models for part of speech tagging and parsing.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of embeddings and ensembling, which are also commonly used in computer vision tasks.
